TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {38416=PERSONAL    Majoring in history ... son of Hans Schwieger and Merritt Alves … born on January 30, 1990 … grandfather Tom Schwieger played at Drake … chose Dartmouth over Harvard.}
textBeforeTable: Complete Career Statistics Finished career as Dartmouth's all-time leading rusher with 3,150 yards ... also accumulated more all-purpose yards (4,115) than anyone in Big Green history ... both totals placed him 12th in Ivy League history at the completion of his career ... among the 14 players in Ivy history to be named the league’s Player of the Week five or more times ... one of the seven to amass 16 100-yard games in a career ... scored 26 touchdowns in his four seasons, all on the ground, the second most rushing TDs in Dartmouth history ... his 156 points ranks sixth at the college as well. SENIOR (2011) Associated Press All-America Third Team ... College Sports Madness All-America Second Team ... New England Team FCS All-Star Team for second straight year ... finalist for the Bushnell Cup ... fifth player in Dartmouth history to be All-Ivy First Team three times ... given the Coach Bob Blackman Trophy for a second consecutive season as the player, selected by the coaching staff, who has contributed most to the success of the team ... Preseason FCS All-America Third Team and Preseason All-Ivy First Team as chosen by Phil Steele’s College Football ...
